<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br><br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br><br>
If the source does not include a publication date, omit the date and include an access date at the end of the Works Cited entry. If you have found the date from a reliable external source, place the date in square brackets to show that the date did not come from the source. If there is uncertainty about the date, place a question mark after the date. For further information, see 2.6.1 in the <a href="http://west-sydney-primo.hosted.exlibrisgroup.com/UWS-ALMA:default_scope:UWS-ALMA21186157620001571" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MLA Handbook (8th edition)</a>.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<em>Title of the page</em>. Organisation or publisher of site, URL. Access date.  
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of the page">Statistics New Zealand</span>.</em> 
	<span class="hover" title="Organisation or publisher of site">New Zealand Government</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Date of access">26 Sep. 2044</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="URL">www.stats.govt.nz/Census/2044-census/profile-and-summary-reports/quickstats-about-a-place.aspx?request_value=14973&tabname=</span>. 
</blockquote>
